# Trivy ignore file. One ID per line. Comments start with '#'.
# Rationale mirrors the intentional skips in checkov.yaml so posture decisions
# are documented in one coherent place.

# CloudFront WAF is opt-in via module variable `enable_waf`; a default WAFv2
# web ACL carries non-trivial cost and AWS-managed rule subscription fees, so
# the module ships it off. Matches CKV_AWS_68 skip in checkov.yaml.
AVD-AWS-0011

# S3 bucket uses SSE-S3 (AES256) by default because the static site stores no
# customer data and a customer-managed KMS key would add monthly cost and key
# rotation overhead for no marginal risk reduction. Matches CKV_AWS_145 skip.
AVD-AWS-0132
